{
    "id": "utility",
    "lang": "en-us",
    "name": "Utility",
    "description": "A grab-bag of everyday helpers: call other scripts' methods (now or after a delay), add trails/outlines, read asset info, show or hide the mouse cursor, and make unique IDs.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/utility",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "utility",
        "helpers",
        "callmethod",
        "cursor"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "Time",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/time"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "UniObjectUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-us/uniobjectutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Utility"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`Utility` is a collection of handy, everyday helpers that don't belong to one specific topic. With it you can run another script's method (right away or after a delay), add visual extras like trails and outlines, look up information about an asset, control the mouse cursor, and generate unique IDs."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Where you see `uniscript` in a method, it means **a script** — usually `this` (the script you're writing), or a reference to another object's script that you want to act on."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Running a method by its name"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Sometimes you want to trigger a method on another script — for example, telling an enemy to `TakeDamage`. These helpers let you do that by name."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                [
                    "`CallMethod(script, methodName, data)`",
                    "Runs the named method on `script` right now and gives back whatever it returns. `data` is an extra value to pass along (use `null` if none)."
                ],
                [
                    "`CallMethodDelayed(script, methodName, data, delay)`",
                    "Same, but waits `delay` seconds first — perfect for \"do this in 3 seconds\"."
                ],
                [
                    "`HasMethod(script, methodName)`",
                    "Returns `true` if that script actually has the method, so you can check before calling."
                ]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Tell another object's script to take damage.",
                "Utility.CallMethod(enemyScript, \"TakeDamage\", 10);",
                "",
                "// Despawn this object 3 seconds from now.",
                "Utility.CallMethodDelayed(this, \"Despawn\", null, 3.0);",
                "",
                "// Only call it if it exists.",
                "if (Utility.HasMethod(enemyScript, \"Heal\"))",
                "{",
                "    Utility.CallMethod(enemyScript, \"Heal\", 5);",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Adding visual extras"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "These attach an extra visual feature to an object. Call them once (usually in setup), then configure the feature through its own component."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it adds"
            ],
            "rows": [
                [
                    "`AddLineRenderer(this)`",
                    "A line you can draw between points — for ropes, lasers, or connections."
                ],
                [
                    "`AddTrailRenderer(this)`",
                    "A trail that streaks behind the object as it moves."
                ],
                [
                    "`AddOutline(this)`",
                    "A glowing outline around the object — great for highlighting."
                ],
                [
                    "`RefreshOutlineMesh(this)`",
                    "Rebuilds the outline if the object's shape changed."
                ]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Asset information"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it returns"
            ],
            "rows": [
                [
                    "`GetAssetName(asset)`",
                    "The asset's display name as text."
                ],
                [
                    "`GetAssetType(asset)`",
                    "What kind of asset it is, as text."
                ],
                [
                    "`GetMotionDuration(asset)`",
                    "How many seconds an animation clip lasts — useful for timing what happens after it."
                ],
                [
                    "`LoadAssetAndCallback(asset, script, callbackMethod)`",
                    "Loads an asset in the background and calls `callbackMethod` on `script` when it's ready."
                ]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Mouse cursor"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Control whether the player's mouse pointer is shown. Hiding it (and locking it) is common during gameplay; showing it again is useful for menus."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Hide and lock the cursor during play.",
                "Utility.SetCursorVisibility(false);",
                "",
                "// Show it again for a menu.",
                "Utility.SetCursorVisibility(true);",
                "",
                "bool shown = Utility.GetCursorVisibility();"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Unique IDs"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-017",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`GenerateUniqueID()` returns a brand-new, one-of-a-kind text ID every time it's called — handy for tagging spawned items, save slots, or anything that must never collide."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-018",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "string id = Utility.GenerateUniqueID();"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-019",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-020",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`object`", "`CallMethod`", "`uniscript, string methodName, object refData`"],
                ["`bool`", "`HasMethod`", "`uniscript, string methodName`"],
                ["`void`", "`CallMethodDelayed`", "`uniscript, string methodName, object refData, float delay`"],
                ["`string`", "`GetAssetName`", "`object asset`"],
                ["`string`", "`GetAssetType`", "`object asset`"],
                ["`void`", "`LoadAssetAndCallback`", "`object asset, uniscript, string callbackMethod`"],
                ["`string`", "`GenerateUniqueID`", "—"],
                ["`void`", "`AddLineRenderer`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddTrailRenderer`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`AddOutline`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`void`", "`RefreshOutlineMesh`", "`uniscript`"],
                ["`float`", "`GetMotionDuration`", "`object asset`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetCursorVisibility`", "`bool state`"],
                ["`bool`", "`GetCursorVisibility`", "—"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-021",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`CallMethodDelayed` is one of the easiest ways to schedule something for later without writing your own timer. For repeating or frame-based timing instead, see [Time](/docs/uniscript/en-us/time)."
        }
    ]
}
